Component:

    @Component({...})
    export class AppComponent {
      options = [
        {key: &quot;one&quot;, value: &quot;First option&quot;},
        {key: &quot;two&quot;, value: &quot;Second option&quot;},
        {key: &quot;three&quot;, value: &quot;Third option&quot;}
      ];
    
      selectedOption = &quot;one&quot;;
    }

Template:

    &lt;select [(ngModel)]=&quot;selectedOption&quot;&gt;
      &lt;option *ngFor=&quot;let opt of options&quot; value=&quot;{{opt.key}}&quot;&gt;{{ opt.value }}&lt;/option&gt;
    &lt;/select&gt;
    &lt;p *ngIf=&quot;selectedOption === &#39;one&#39;&quot;&gt;First option selected&lt;/p&gt;
    etc.

Then, you can simply assign a new value to the `selectedOption` from your component code, and its template will update accordingly.

Check this quick example:
https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-xxhbgp


